Becky Shaw, II. 1864 grad
uate of North High School, re-
Gently enrolled in the freshman
class at Spelman College, at
Atlanta, Ga.


While in high school she was
active in the YWCA and attended
an international convention in
Hawaii, as a delegate.


She also participated in the
Girls League and served as a
member of the Rhodes Store
fashion board.


Miss Shaw is the recipient of
a $625 Field Scholarship. She
is the daughter Of Mr.. and Mrs.
Augustus H. Shaw. 1447 E.
Cor onado.

It's easy to cook eggs and bacon
at the same time-and save dish
washing-with my new Club
Aluminium divided fry pan.
There are three sections, so you
can fry your egg while you
scramble mine. Or you can do
bacon and sausage at the same

Year after year Americans eat
record amounts of cheese.
During 1868 consumption rose to
an all time high of o.4 pounds
per person. This yearly per

capita increase has been going on
almost continuously over the last
two decades. In fact, since the
end of World War II, cheese con-
sumption has risen by more than
one-third.
